<TITLE> One dies in Pabna river boat collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Madaripur, June 11 (bdnews24.com)--At least one person died and 15 others were injured when a speedboat and a trawler collided in the Padma River near Shibchar Upazila on Thursday night. The accident occurred around 10pm at Kaorakandi-Mawa ferry docks in the Upazila's Chairmanghat area. The deceased was identified as Bacchu Fakir, 30, son of Hashem Fakir, resident of Kandi village. Three others were critically injured. The speedboat, carrying passengers, left Mawa Ferry dock at around 9:30pm and collided head-on with the trawler at Kathalbari's Chairman-Ghat area, Shibchar police said. Shibchar highway police sergeant Asadul Islam told bdnews24.com that the injured have been admitted into Faridpur Medical College Hospital and Bhanga Upazila Health Complex. bdnews
